* voting is moral
	* the vote does not authorize anything, it only expresses a preference [among the candidates]
	* you are a citizen, hence you own part of the country, you are a shareholder of it, you have the right to vote about the common property [the country, ...]
* you should take opportunities to make the world better
	* with voting you have the opportunity to influence
		* some people see this opportunity small, because the probabilty of his vote actually mattering is small, because the voter set is large; but these people fail to see that if it matters then it matter much, that large, as the voter set